WEBVTT

00:01.768 --> 00:03.609
Previously on Madam Secretary:

00:03.610 --> 00:05.101
One truckload of spent fuel rods

00:05.102 --> 00:06.638
stolen by Moldovan thugs

00:06.639 --> 00:09.558
with no expertise in handling the material

00:09.559 --> 00:12.478
is hardly what I would
deem a priority situation.

00:12.479 --> 00:14.808
If the uranium comes with
its own nuclear physicist

00:14.809 --> 00:16.478
to show 'em how to use it...

00:16.479 --> 00:18.348
I'd call that getting the
most bang for your buck.

00:18.349 --> 00:21.098
Mom is hosting a conference this
week featuring Noura Al-Kitabi.

00:21.099 --> 00:22.348
I think we should all go.

00:22.349 --> 00:24.388
Isn't that the girl who got acid attacked?

00:24.389 --> 00:26.848
In Saudi Arabia, we
learned that Hizb Al-Shahid

00:26.849 --> 00:29.638
is targeting the family
of Noura Al-Kitabi.

00:29.639 --> 00:31.558
Now you're telling me
that that's the same group

00:31.559 --> 00:32.888
that was trying to buy the uranium?

00:32.889 --> 00:35.268
The conference... shut it down. Now.

00:36.455 --> 00:37.638
Ma'am!

00:37.639 --> 00:39.888
This way, everybody. We need to get out.

00:39.889 --> 00:42.699
Allahu Akbar!

00:43.809 --> 00:45.308
No.

00:45.309 --> 00:47.231
Come on.

00:47.232 --> 00:50.699
Please pick up. Pick up.

00:52.189 --> 00:55.808
Come on, come on, pick up, pick up, please.

00:55.809 --> 00:57.888
Hey, it's Stevie. You can leave a message,

00:57.889 --> 00:59.972
- but you really should be texting me.
- Oh, damn it.

00:59.973 --> 01:01.764
Stevie, listen, as soon as you get this

01:01.765 --> 01:04.950
I need you to call me
back, baby, okay? Really...

01:04.950 --> 01:05.746
I need you to call me back

01:05.747 --> 01:08.288
and let me know that
you guys are okay, okay?

01:08.289 --> 01:10.535
It's Ali. And you have the talking stick.

01:10.536 --> 01:11.389
Leave a message at the beep.

01:11.390 --> 01:13.070
Why can I not get in touch with my family?

01:14.496 --> 01:15.915
Oh, for God's sake, now what?

01:15.916 --> 01:17.205
The network keeps crashing.

01:17.206 --> 01:19.995
Wh...

01:19.996 --> 01:21.590
Turn around. We're gonna go
to St. Anne's in Virginia.

01:21.591 --> 01:22.883
Negative, ma'am. We're

01:22.884 --> 01:24.881
under strict protocol to get
you to the White House bunker.

01:24.882 --> 01:26.833
No, no, I don't care.
Just turn around, now.

01:26.834 --> 01:28.245
I'm sorry, ma'am. Not your call.

01:28.246 --> 01:29.785
There could be a secondary attack.

01:29.786 --> 01:32.067
- Do you really think that might happen?
- It did on 9/11.

01:33.246 --> 01:34.955
Whoa, whoa. Uh, Nadine.

01:34.956 --> 01:36.458
- You keep trying, okay?
- Yeah.

01:40.496 --> 01:42.285
Nadine, what is it? What do you have?

01:42.286 --> 01:45.495
Uh, we're getting reports
of dozens of severe injuries.

01:45.496 --> 01:47.075
Uh, but no details yet.

01:47.076 --> 01:49.785
We're putting all of our
foreign outposts on high alert.

01:49.786 --> 01:51.535
No, no, no, forget high alerts, okay?

01:51.536 --> 01:54.535
I want every embassy and
consulate on lockdown.

01:54.536 --> 01:55.536
Yes, ma'am.

01:55.537 --> 01:56.745
Hey, hey, wait.

01:56.746 --> 01:58.165
Don't go anywhere. Stay there, stay there.

01:58.166 --> 01:59.205
I got to call you back.

01:59.206 --> 02:00.581
Jason.

02:00.582 --> 02:01.955
Jason.

02:01.956 --> 02:04.375
Hey, baby. How are you?

02:04.376 --> 02:05.705
We just went through triage.

02:05.706 --> 02:07.375
They're saying the bomb is radioactive.

02:07.376 --> 02:09.285
Do you feel sick?

02:09.286 --> 02:10.495
Do your sisters?

02:10.496 --> 02:12.535
No, no, we all tested negative.

02:12.536 --> 02:13.806
Dad got us out in time.

02:13.807 --> 02:15.075
Okay.

02:15.076 --> 02:18.455
It's bad, Mom. I mean, we've
seen people with, like...

02:18.456 --> 02:20.495
there's a lot of blood.

02:20.496 --> 02:22.785
I know. Listen, deep breaths.

02:22.786 --> 02:26.455
Listen, baby, I got to go to
the White House for a little bit

02:26.456 --> 02:29.665
and then I'm gonna get to you
as soon as I can, all right?

02:29.666 --> 02:33.165
You just... put Dad on the phone, okay?

02:33.166 --> 02:36.516
Mom, Dad went back inside.

02:38.166 --> 02:39.271
What do you mean?

02:39.272 --> 02:40.375
After the bomb went off.

02:40.376 --> 02:42.415
I don't know, he wanted to help.

02:43.851 --> 02:45.951
Where is he now?

